What Newton is arguing in the above excerpt is that as Substack moved up th=
e stack its moderation responsibilities shifted. The problem, though, is th=
at Newton also threatened Stripe (in the second article I excerpted above).=
 Stripe is not running a social network, they=E2=80=99re not promoting post=
s, they=E2=80=99re not algorithmically featuring content =E2=80=94 they=E2=
=80=99re not hosting content at all. They=E2=80=99re an infrastructure prov=
ider! I=E2=80=99m not saying Stripe shouldn=E2=80=99t have policies =E2=80=
=94 infrastructure is in the middle of the stack, not the bottom =E2=80=94 =
but I think it is alarming that the idea was even mooted.

Unfortunately, it does seem inevitable that, at some point in the future, m=
